	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Police arrested four people in Jeffreys Bay in the Eastern Cape on Monday for the alleged possession of tik and seized a vehicle allegedly used to transport the drugs. It was estimated that the tik was worth about R327 000. Police spokesperson Sergeant Majola Nkohli said Crime Prevention police received information about a blue Toyota Corolla Quest. It was suspected that the car was used to transport drugs into Jeffreys Bay through St Francis Street. READ: Booze, drugs and perlemoen: More than 120 arrested over weekend in Cape Town "Members used an unmarked vehicle to follow up the information, spotted the vehicle fitting the description and upon searching the vehicle, found the tik." "A preliminary investigation has revealed that the motor vehicle was unroadworthy. The four suspects, aged between 29 and 36, are due to appear [in] the Humansdorp Magistrate's Court [on Tuesday] on charges of possession of crystal methamphetamine (tik)," said Nkohli. Humansdorp cluster commander, Brigadier John Lebok, said he was pleased to see that some residents were working with the police to fight the proliferation of drugs. KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.